\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Or your mother madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 In West Auckland who were considered the most important people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well Doctor Smith and Doctor Clarke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Not that I know of. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Did you come into contact with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Yes. Quite regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Why do you think they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Why do I think they were important? Well I think the
y were good men because - they looked after my mother well, makes me think that. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What do you mean they were good men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 They were good men. They were good living men as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with, who did they have for friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Shopkeepers? Such as us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Who did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 the clergy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  of have for friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well he was generally used to visit all did Mr Rosecamp. But I wasn't church, I was Methodist. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Who did the clergy at the chapel associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 All of us. We were all Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Who did the teachers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 have for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well I couldn't tell you who they would have for friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 You never noticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What about the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Farmers? Yes, I lived against some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Who did they have for friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 Couldn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  tell you, only - they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 everybody\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  friend was Pease's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What about the employers, the bosses, who did they have for friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh that's something I can't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well all that I know was good people. And lived good. There'd be others you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What do you mean by living good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well they lived up to - to what they professed to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What about the people who went to chapel, what sort of people went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Just ordinary working people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 
Where you lived in West Auckland did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 No, we were all nearly alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do you think that any one group }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 felt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  itself superior t the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Not - no, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Did you ever know of a rough family? What would make them be classed as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Did you ever remember a family that was called a rough family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well I tell you, we mixed among them all in a - in a little - it was a village then but it's a huge place now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do you remember any particular family that you thought of as being rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Rough. But they weren't kiddies, they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 wren}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What made them rough men?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 'Cos they used to fight after pubs closed. And father used to get us in afore we met. You see,
 before the pubs come out, he used to have us in bed. Never allowed out after a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 certain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 
 time. There used to be rows on a Saturday night about half past ten in middle of green there was a fight. You know, they could drink then for dink and drink and drink, 
you know. Dint' close 'til about eleven. They were the rough people. I wouldn't like to - any of them today, they'd cut me head off - if they were alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do you remember a distinction f this kind, rough and respectable, between craftsmen and labourers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh no. I don't think anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 No, we were all one on here, I've told you before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 How did they treat the people in the sort of snobby class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 particular}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh my grandfather was a miner - was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 tailor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  but she was no different to anybody else. He was a hand tailor a sewer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 That was a skilled job in those days wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh he was a grand man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 
Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another, was it possible to move up the social scale and do you remember any-one who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 No, I can't say we could, there's lots of good people but I couldn't distinct one from another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 You don't remember anyone about who people said, he's a real gentleman, or she's a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh we used to say that about the vicar.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 He was a good man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do you ever remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Policeman? Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well he didn't used to bother us because we were never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 out}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  late to see them. We used to know they were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 When you were naughty did your mother or father ever say, I - 1'llcall a policeman? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Or grandma, did they ever say I'll call a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 policeman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  if you're naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Have you any idea how the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh they were grand. Yes. 'Cos me granny went - you know, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 they}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  used to bring her to - him - and if she saw him she were finished. Me gran
ny. You know, she lost her memory, she was very old. And they used to bring P.C. Ainsley and he used to take his coat off. When he come to see her, so she wouldn't - be upset. And she once said to him, funny like, and who might you be? And he says, I'm P.
C. Ainsley. And she says, then where's your buttons. He says, you're not so soft, Annie. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5798061\charrsid15683539 He}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539  knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 So he was well liked was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Rather liked - yes. He took his coat so as he wouldn't frighten her. Lived again around about each other you know,
 it's only a country place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Was your home rented in Post Office Square?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Did you ever see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Yes. Lived against him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh he was all right was Old John.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Was your father ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Do }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12221869\charrsid15683539 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 
 ever remember getting any help from the guardians or the parish or any charity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Oh no. No. None needed.
