\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well just have ordinary - something plain, maybe the cheese and bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What did you drink at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12221869\charrsid15683539 suppertime}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Well I couldn't tell you. It would be tea likely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Did you have anything different for your dinner on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Just a roast on a Sunday. And Yorkshire pudding. Always had something on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4654119 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 What about tea on a Sunday, was that ever different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5591740 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 Something out of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12221869\charrsid15683539 ordinary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6965864\charrsid15683539 , you know what I mean. We used to make trifles and that for tea. Oh we lived all right, don't worry.
